Uses of Class
functions.Nexus

  • Packages that use Nexus 
    Package Description
    functions
    This package contains all classes nessecary, to work with mathematical functions, with the most important class being Function

    • Uses of Nexus in functions

      Subclasses of Nexus in functions 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  AdditionNexus
      Stores multiple FunctionParts.
      class  Chaining
      This class represents a chaining of two functions, one being the inner function, the second, the outer function.
      This means the result of the inner function will be used as input for the outer function.
      f(x) = f(u(x))
      Note: This FunctionPart returns null in getAntiderivative(), because this is extremely complex.
      class  FactorNexus
      Class representing a multiplication of multiple FunctionParts
      This function is constructed like following: f(x) = u(x) * v(x) * ...
